9
00:01:06,520 --> 00:01:06,940
Mostar.

10
00:01:08,400 --> 00:01:16,840
Mostar in Bosnia and Herzegovina is
renowned for its old bridge, Stari Most, a symbol of the city's historical periods of division and unity.

11
00:01:17,240 --> 00:01:26,660
The bridge spans the Nuretva River and
connects two parts of the city, embodying the reconciliation between diverse cultural, religious, and ethnic groups after the Yugoslav Wars.

12
00:01:27,120 --> 00:01:28,380
Rebuilt in 2004,

13
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:33,900
it is a replica of the 16th century
Ottoman bridge that was destroyed in 1993.

14
00:01:34,320 --> 00:01:38,280
Surrounding the bridge, Mostar's Old Town
features cobblestone streets,

15
00:01:38,840 --> 00:01:42,060
traditional shops, and historic buildings
that reflect Ottoman,

16
00:01:42,680 --> 00:01:42,980
Mediterranean,

17
00:01:43,520 --> 00:01:45,920
and Western European architectural
influences.

18
00:01:46,320 --> 00:01:54,180
The area is notable for its multicultural
heritage with significant landmarks such as the Kosky Memid Pasha Mosque and the Old Bazaar, Kujun Zaluk.

19
00:01:54,480 --> 00:02:02,500
These sites offer a glimpse into the
city's past from its Ottoman roots, to its present -day status, as a symbol of coexistence and cultural diversity.

20
00:02:02,940 --> 00:02:12,280
Mostar's inclusion on the UNESCO world
