21
00:02:13,160 --> 00:02:14,220
Number 9.

22
00:02:14,520 --> 00:02:15,140
Mediora

23
00:02:16,620 --> 00:02:23,340
Mediora, located in central Greece, is
extraordinary for its vertiginous monasteries set atop towering rock formations.

24
00:02:23,820 --> 00:02:31,940
These geological marvels formed over
millions of years from weathering and earthquakes, create a landscape of immense, natural beauty, and spiritual solitude.

25
00:02:32,300 --> 00:02:40,160
Established in the 14th century, the
monasteries of Mediora were built by monks seeking refuge in isolation, accessible only by ladders and ropes.

26
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:40,820
Today,

27
00:02:41,320 --> 00:02:50,620
six of these monasteries remain active,
serving as a testament to the Byzantine monastic tradition and offering visitors a glimpse into the ascetic life of the monks who reside there.

28
00:02:50,920 --> 00:02:57,840
The architecture of the monasteries is a
remarkable adaptation to the natural environment, with buildings constructed around the contours of the rocks.

29
00:02:58,260 --> 00:03:00,900
Inside, they house priceless collections
of manuscripts,

30
00:03:01,460 --> 00:03:07,180
icons, and religious artifacts, preserving
the cultural and religious heritage of the Orthodox Christian tradition.

31
00:03:07,720 --> 00:03:14,200
Mediora's inclusion in the UNESCO World
Heritage List highlights its dual significance as a natural and cultural monument.

32
00:03:14,680 --> 00:03:24,200
The site represents a unique harmony
between human faith and the natural world, attracting thousands of visitors annually, who come to marvel at its landscapes and spiritual history.

33
00:03:25,700 --> 00:03:26,400
Number 8.

34
00:03:26,660 --> 00:03:27,740
Dubrovnik Old Town

35
00:03:28,660.0000000000291 --> 00:03:39,400
Dubrovnik, often referred to as the Pearl
of the Adriatic, is distinguished by its remarkable Old Town, encircled by formidable stone walls constructed between the 11th and 17th centuries.

36
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:48,940
This UNESCO World Heritage Site in Croatia
exemplifies a well -preserved medieval urban landscape, boasting an array of gothic, renaissance, and baroque churches,

37
00:03:49,440 --> 00:03:51,760
monasteries, palaces, and fountains.

38
00:03:52,080 --> 00:03:59,480
Dubrovnik's strategic maritime position
fostered its development as a significant Mediterranean sea power from the Middle Ages onwards.

39
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:08,260
The city's layout reflects the need for
defense and trade, with its main street stradun, linking the western entrance, pile gate, to the eastern gate, close gate.

40
00:04:08,580 --> 00:04:15,340
Landmarks such as the Sponsor Palace and
the Rector's Palace illustrate the city's historic affluence and cultural sophistication.

41
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:16,839.9999999999709
Dubrovnik's fortifications,

42
00:04:17,399.9999999999709 --> 00:04:27,240
including the impressive Minceda Tower and
Fort LaVriginac, offer panoramic views of the Adriatic Sea and serve as a testament to the city's strategic military importance.

43
00:04:27,780 --> 00:04:36,920
Dubrovnik's Old Town is not just a
historical site, but also a vibrant cultural hub, hosting numerous festivals and events that celebrate its rich heritage.

44
00:04:37,320 --> 00:04:47,780
Its preservation as a UNESCO site
underscores the universal value of its architectural and historical legacy, attracting visitors worldwide to experience its timeless beauty.

45
00:04:49,020 --> 00:04:49,780
7.

46
00:04:50,340 --> 00:04:50,540
Prague.

47
00:04:51,640 --> 00:04:59,480
Prague, the capital of the Czech Republic,
is celebrated for its exceptional historic core, which spans over a thousand years of architectural development.

48
00:04:59,740 --> 00:05:08,720
This UNESCO World Heritage site is
characterized by its well -preserved layout, showcasing a blend of gothic, renaissance, baroque, and art nouveau buildings.

49
00:05:09,260 --> 00:05:18,220
Central to Prague's historical
significance is the Prague Castle, an ancient symbol of Czech statehood and the seat of political and religious power since the 9th century.

50
00:05:18,620 --> 00:05:23,400
The city's historic center includes the
Old Town, the Lesser Town, and the New Town,

51
00:05:23,960 --> 00:05:25,480
notable for their beautiful squares,

52
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:28,280
narrow streets, and numerous historic
buildings.

53
00:05:28,760 --> 00:05:38,800
The Charles Bridge, dating back to the
14th century, is one of Prague's most iconic structures, providing a pedestrian link between the Old Town and the Lesser Town across the Valtava River.

54
00:05:39,180 --> 00:05:47,180
The Old Town Square, with the astronomical
clock, is another focal point, offering an insight into Prague's vibrant urban life throughout the centuries.

55
00:05:47,520 --> 00:05:54,740
Prague's architectural and urban
coherence, along with its rich cultural heritage, make it a prime example of urban continuity and development.

56
00:05:54,740 --> 00:06:04,780
It's inclusion on the UNESCO World
Heritage List highlights its global significance as a cultural and historical monument, drawing visitors to experience its unique charm and beauty.

57
00:06:05,780 --> 00:06:06,440
6.

58
00:06:06,900 --> 00:06:15,240
Stonehenge Located on Salisbury Plain in
Wiltshire, England, Stonehenge is one of the most famous prehistoric monuments in the world.

59
00:06:15,480 --> 00:06:27,540
This UNESCO World Heritage site consists
of an outer ring of sars and standing stones, each around 13 feet high, seven feet wide, and weighing approximately 25 tons, topped by connecting horizontal lentil stones.

60
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:33,740
Inside this circle are five trillathons,
pairs of larger sars and stones with a third stone across the top.

61
00:06:34,140 --> 00:06:40,100
Numerous burial mounds surround the
structure, hinting at its use as a burial site from as early as 3000 BC.

62
00:06:40,560 --> 00:06:49,780
Archaeologists believe Stonehenge was
constructed in several stages, with the earliest known structure being a circular ditch and bank, dating back to about 3,100 BC.

63
00:06:50,240 --> 00:06:55,560
The stone circle itself was erected in the
late Neolithic period, around 2500 BC.

64
00:06:56,040 --> 00:07:05,380
While its precise purpose remains a
subject of debate, theory suggests it served as a temple aligned with solar phenomena, an astronomical observatory, or a sacred burial ground.

65
00:07:05,820 --> 00:07:14,880
Stonehenge's sophisticated construction
techniques and its alignment with the solstices highlight the astronomical knowledge and spiritual significance it held for prehistoric peoples.

66
00:07:15,220 --> 00:07:21,400
It's enduring mystery and archaeological
significance make it a pivotal site for understanding Britain's prehistoric culture.

67
00:07:22,900 --> 00:07:24,040
Number 5.

68
00:07:24,300 --> 00:07:25,360
Kremlin and Red Square

69
00:07:26,060 --> 00:07:33,400
The Kremlin and Red Square, located at the
very heart of Moscow, Russia, are emblematic of the country's political and historical narrative.

70
00:07:33,740 --> 00:07:44,380
This UNESCO World Heritage site comprises
the Kremlin, a historic fortified complex that has been the seat of power for Russian rulers and Red Square, the country's most famous public space.

71
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:55,560
The Kremlin's walls and towers, dating
back to the 15th century, enclosed palaces, churches, and government buildings representing various architectural styles from the 15th to 20th centuries.

72
00:07:56,020 --> 00:07:59,960
Red Square is bordered by significant
landmarks, including the Ornate St.

73
00:08:00,180 --> 00:08:04,640
Basil's Cathedral, with its iconic onion
-shaped domes, the state historical museum,

74
00:08:05,240 --> 00:08:08,340
Lenin's Mausoleum, and the luxurious gum
department store.

75
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:14,400
The square has been the scene of numerous
historical events, from military parades to political demonstrations,

76
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:16,940
reflecting the tumultuous history of
Russia.

77
00:08:17,360 --> 00:08:27,440
The ensemble of the Kremlin and Red Square
is significant for its representation of Russian art and architecture, as well as its influence on the historical and cultural development of Russia and the world.

78
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:34,39.99999999994179
It stands as a testament to the country's
complex history, from the Tsarist regime through the Soviet era to the present day.

79
00:08:35,419.9999999999418 --> 00:08:36,80.00000000005821
Number 4.

80
00:08:36,340.0000000000582 --> 00:08:36,980
Capitokia

81
00:08:38,220 --> 00:08:50,240
Situated in Central Turkey, Capitokia is
renowned for its extraordinary landscapes, formed by volcanic eruptions, followed by erosion, creating a fairy tale terrain of rock formations known as fairy chimneys.

82
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:59,020
This UNESCO World Heritage Site
encompasses a region of exceptional natural wonders, including valleys, canyons, and distinctive rock formations,

83
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:04,460
alongside a rich human history that has
ingeniously adapted to the challenging environment.

84
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:14,060
The area is dotted with homes, churches,
and entire cities carved out of the soft rock, dating back to the Hittite era through early Christianity and the Byzantine period.

85
00:09:14,360 --> 00:09:25,680
The Gurum National Park, at the heart of
Capitokia, showcases this remarkable blend of natural and cultural heritage, with rock -hewn chapels and monasteries adorned with frescoes, depicting Christian themes.

86
00:09:26,080 --> 00:09:38,680
The underground cities of Daringkuyu and
Kaimakli, which could house thousands of people along with their livestock and food stores, highlight the region's historical strategic significance, and the inhabitants' ability to adapt to threats.

87
00:09:39,140 --> 00:09:49,140
Capitokia is not only a testament to the
natural beauty and cultural ingenuity of the region, but also a prime example of human resilience and creativity in adapting to the environment.

88
00:09:49,440 --> 00:09:56,600
Its unique landscape continues to attract
tourists and scholars alike, fascinated by its geological, historical, and cultural richness.

89
00:09:58,120 --> 00:09:59,320
Number 3.

90
00:09:59,540 --> 00:10:00,180
Molse Michel

91
00:10:00,960 --> 00:10:03,500
This island commune in Normandy, France,

92
00:10:04,040 --> 00:10:08,340
stands as a striking example of medieval
architecture and strategic fortification.

93
00:10:08,720 --> 00:10:18,380
This UNESCO World Heritage site is
renowned for its Benedictine Abbey, which dominates the island's skyline and its unique title phenomenon that can isolate the commune from the mainland.

94
00:10:18,860 --> 00:10:29,500
The construction of the Abbey began in the
11th century and continued over several centuries, showcasing a remarkable blend of Romanesque, Gothic, and flamboyant Gothic architectural styles.

95
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:39,880
The island's strategic location, at the
mouth of the Kuznan River, made it a site of military significance and a symbol of French national identity, especially during the Hundred Years' War.

96
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:49,610
The winding streets and fortified walls of
the medieval town below the Abbey reflect the complex history and architectural development of Molse Michel over the millennia.

97
00:10:50,050 --> 00:10:57,830
Molse Michel's unique natural setting,
combined with its architectural beauty and historical importance, has made it a pilgrimage site for centuries.

98
00:10:58,510 --> 00:11:05,950
Today, it continues to captivate visitors
from around the world, offering insights into medieval religious life, architectural innovation,

99
00:11:06,470 --> 00:11:07,970
and the enduring human spirit.

100
00:11:09,710 --> 00:11:10,270
Number 2.

101
00:11:10,510 --> 00:11:11,430
Acropolis of Athens

102
00:11:12,300 --> 00:11:17,950
The Acropolis of Athens is an ancient
citadel located on a rocky outcrop above the city of Athens

103
00:11:18,510 --> 00:11:21,730
and is renowned for its architectural and
historical significance.

104
00:11:22,210 --> 00:11:31,370
This UNESCO World Heritage Site houses the
remains of several ancient buildings of great architectural and historic value, the most famous being the Parthenon.

105
00:11:31,630 --> 00:11:35,130
Constructed in the 5th century BC during
the Golden Age of Athens,

106
00:11:35,630 --> 00:11:38,490
the Parthenon is a temple dedicated to the
goddess Athena,

107
00:11:38,990 --> 00:11:41,110
whom the people of Athens considered their
patron.

108
00:11:41,570 --> 00:11:48,410
Other significant structures on the
Acropolis include the Aurectheon, a complex marble building known for its carry -outed porch,

109
00:11:49,050 --> 00:11:55,650
the Temple of Athena Nike, dedicated to
the goddess of victory, and the Prophelya, the Grand Entrance Way to the Acropolis.

110
00:11:56,250 --> 00:12:04,970
These monuments are exemplary of ancient
Greek art and architecture and symbolize the achievements of classical Athens in democracy, philosophy, and arts.

111
00:12:05,510 --> 00:12:15,150
The Acropolis stands as a testament to the
creativity and power of the ancient Greeks and continues to be a symbol of the cultural and political achievements of the Western civilization.

112
00:12:15,570 --> 00:12:23,710
Its preservation and study offer
invaluable insights into ancient history, architecture, and mythology, drawing millions of visitors and scholars every year.

113
00:12:25,130 --> 00:12:26,450
Number 1 Alhambra

114
00:12:27,390 --> 00:12:37,970
The Alhambra, located in Granada, Spain,
is a stunning complex of palaces, courtyards, and gardens, embodying the zenith of Morish art and architecture in the Iberian Peninsula.

115
00:12:37,970 --> 00:12:50,730
This UNESCO World Heritage Site was
primarily built during the mid -14th century under the Nazareth dynasty, showcasing the Islamic culture's sophistication and aesthetic sensibilities before the Christian reconquista.

116
00:12:51,190 --> 00:12:53,730
The Alhambra's name, meaning the red one
in Arabic,

117
00:12:54,350 --> 00:12:58,430
refers to the red clay used in its
construction, which glows red at sunset.

118
00:12:59,210 --> 00:13:02,490
The Alhambra served as a royal residence,
court, and fortress.

119
00:13:02,950 --> 00:13:12,290
Its architecture is a blend of the
delicate beauty and power, with the palace of the lions and the court of the Mertles being prime examples of Islamic architectural innovation and art.

120
00:13:12,570 --> 00:13:19,770
The preservation of the Alhambra allows
for a deep appreciation of Morish culture and its lasting influence on Spanish heritage.

121
00:13:19,970 --> 00:13:23,170
It stands as a testament to the historical
confluence of Islam,

122
00:13:23,690 --> 00:13:25,650
Christianity, and Judaism in Spain,

123
00:13:26,250 --> 00:13:30,010
offering insights into the complexity and
richness of Andalusian history.

